OL,3,CThe tidal wave of desperation I've
OL,4,Cwitnessed reporting on SEND crisis
OL,6,FI started telling the stories of
OL,7,Fparents in Somerset who were
OL,8,Fstruggling with getting the education
OL,9,Fthey wanted for their children around
OL,10,Fthe time I became a parent myself.
OL,12,FThere is something about the raw hopes
OL,13,Fand dreams you have for your children
OL,14,Fthat feel like such a given - they'll
OL,15,Fgrow up, they'll go to school, perhaps
OL,16,Fto university and on into
OL,17,Findependence, a career and maybe a
OL,18,Ffamily of their own.
OL,20,FOf course, the reality is not so rose-
OL,21,Ftinted for many families.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/11
