OL,3,CThe tidal wave of desperation I've
OL,4,Cwitnessed reporting on SEND crisis
OL,6,FMany of the children I met either
OL,7,Fdidn't have a school place at all or
OL,8,Ftheir parents were keeping them away
OL,9,Ffrom school because the place assigned
OL,10,Fto them was not suitable. This is
OL,11,Foften because they will have been
OL,12,Fgiven a place at a so-called
OL,13,F'mainstream school' - like your local
OL,14,Fprimary or secondary - but their needs
OL,15,Fare too acute for staff there to
OL,16,Fproperly support them.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
