OL,3,CThe tidal wave of desperation I've
OL,4,Cwitnessed reporting on SEND crisis
OL,6,F"I'm not very confident at all
OL,7,Fanymore, compared to what I used to
OL,8,Fbe," he said. "It feels like when you
OL,9,Fwhack yourself with a hammer - you
OL,10,Ffeel constant pain. Every time I go
OL,11,F'oh, yeah, I could probably do that
OL,12,Fagain,' and then I'm like 'no, you
OL,13,Fcan't do that again, not after that'."
OL,15,FI find it equally heartbreaking that
OL,16,Fsince the very first report I put
OL,17,Ftogether on the issue, other families
OL,18,Fare regularly getting in touch with me
OL,19,Fto say they are in the same position -
OL,20,Fit is a seemingly never-ending tidal
OL,21,Fwave of panic and desperation.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/11
